'''Mecatina''' pronounced (me-kuh-TEE-nuh), is a [[Innu]] word that means large mountain.  It is also the name of two rivers (big and little), a school, and a municipality, on the Lower North Shore of the Gulf of Saint Lawerence of Quebec.  

The Little Mecatina was driven for the first time by Rolf Theiß and Fritz Gottenströter
(with kayaks) from Guetersloh Germany on the 13.8.73-4.9.73


